		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"> 	 <br /><br />I think it's really neat that you can accomplish simple affine transformations just by using Offsets Per Tile mode, combined with X scrolling. I never would have thought that this would work so well.</div>
<br />It works so well because cos(x) is close to 1 if x is close to 0, and because sin(x) is close to x if x is close to 0. (1st degree taylor devlopment).
<br />
<br />I always had the feeling the "offset per tile" mode on the SNES went seriously under-used. Chrono Trigger's title screen, Contra III's first boss, and the elevators in Super Double Dragon's stage 1, it's all I can remember.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


